# Code Review Workflow

## When to Use

- The user wants to review a branch, PR, or work-in-progress changes.
- After `/implement` or before opening a PR.
- The user asks to "review since X" (commit, branch, tag, `main`, etc.).

## Core Approach

Read and follow `.github/skills/code-review/SKILL.md` exactly.

Key points:

- Pin a fixed point; use three-dot diff (`git diff <fixed-point>...HEAD`).
- Fetch spec from issue references, user path, or PRD files.
- Standards sources: `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `docs/ui/GUIDELINES.md`, `docs/testing/README.md`, `CONTEXT.md`, ADRs, vault rules.
- Spawn Standards and Spec sub-agents in parallel via `Task` (`generalPurpose`).
- Aggregate under separate `## Standards` and `## Spec` headings — do not merge findings.

## Skill Files

- `.github/skills/code-review/SKILL.md`
- `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`
